1
00:01:06,336 --> 00:01:10,778
=The Truth=

2
00:01:11,480 --> 00:01:14,136
=Episode 29=

3
00:02:39,726 --> 00:02:40,726
Enough.

4
00:02:41,406 --> 00:02:42,286
Take a rest here.

5
00:02:42,767 --> 00:02:44,566
We're almost at Lei's place.

6
00:02:44,966 --> 00:02:47,286
How about we grab some breakfast
and take a break?

7
00:02:49,047 --> 00:02:49,726
Okay.

8
00:02:50,726 --> 00:02:51,927
Easy now.

9
00:02:54,566 --> 00:02:55,767
Jing, Lei.

10
00:02:55,966 --> 00:02:56,526
You're here.

11
00:02:56,526 --> 00:02:58,286
We were just talking about you two.

12
00:03:06,167 --> 00:03:07,207
Dumplings are ready.

13
00:03:07,327 --> 00:03:08,406
Here, eat it.

14
00:03:13,726 --> 00:03:15,047
How did you know we were coming?

15
00:03:15,966 --> 00:03:17,487
I sent Ye Qian a message

16
00:03:17,526 --> 00:03:19,487
and told him to bring you over
for breakfast.

17
00:03:21,207 --> 00:03:25,367
No wonder he woke me up so early
to go running with him.

18
00:03:26,167 --> 00:03:26,966
Try them.

19
00:03:26,966 --> 00:03:28,216
I made them early this morning.

20
00:03:30,406 --> 00:03:32,207
Here. Try cold dishes I just made.

21
00:03:32,526 --> 00:03:34,047
Eat up. There's more in the pot.

22
00:03:34,047 --> 00:03:34,806
This is yours.

23
00:03:35,167 --> 00:03:37,246
Wait, this is too few.

24
00:03:37,246 --> 00:03:38,286
You eat less.

25
00:03:38,286 --> 00:03:39,607
Or, your blood lipids will spike.

26
00:03:40,047 --> 00:03:40,487
Thanks.

27
00:03:40,487 --> 00:03:41,246
Take your time.

28
00:03:43,487 --> 00:03:48,167
How well you and Jing are living.

29
00:03:48,927 --> 00:03:49,966
Of course.

30
00:03:50,367 --> 00:03:52,327
We've been together
for most of our lives.

31
00:03:52,327 --> 00:03:54,566
Mutual support
through thick and thin, understand?

32
00:03:57,087 --> 00:03:58,126
Ye Qian, what's wrong?

33
00:03:58,726 --> 00:04:00,447
I've been watching you.

34
00:04:01,686 --> 00:04:04,286
You're completely absorbed in cases,
yet have no personal life.

35
00:04:06,806 --> 00:04:07,406
Gone.

36
00:04:08,006 --> 00:04:08,887
He got dumped.

37
00:04:09,286 --> 00:04:10,726
No personal life anymore.

38
00:04:11,846 --> 00:04:13,526
You can't follow your master's example.

39
00:04:14,487 --> 00:04:15,767
He's a blockhead,

40
00:04:16,127 --> 00:04:17,887
totally fixated on cases.

41
00:04:18,606 --> 00:04:19,726
You're still young.

42
00:04:20,166 --> 00:04:22,046
You need both work and a life.

43
00:04:24,046 --> 00:04:25,207
Lei, don't worry.

44
00:04:25,207 --> 00:04:25,966
I'm doing fine.

45
00:04:26,846 --> 00:04:27,647
Alright, eat up.

46
00:04:28,606 --> 00:04:30,327
The dumpling filling is good.

47
00:04:30,887 --> 00:04:32,247
Of course, I made them.

48
00:04:39,366 --> 00:04:40,087
Captain Leng.

49
00:04:40,486 --> 00:04:42,406
We found Wen Yong's phone and wallet.

50
00:04:43,046 --> 00:04:44,166
Where were they?

51
00:04:44,166 --> 00:04:45,687
In the green belt at Central Park.

52
00:04:45,687 --> 00:04:48,286
A landscaping worker found them
while spraying pesticide.

53
00:04:48,286 --> 00:04:49,846
Then he put them at Lost and Found.

54
00:04:50,767 --> 00:04:51,846
Central Park?

55
00:04:51,846 --> 00:04:52,406
Yes.

56
00:04:53,087 --> 00:04:55,046
How far is it
from where Wen Yong disappeared?

57
00:04:55,447 --> 00:04:56,687
About one intersection away,

58
00:04:56,687 --> 00:04:57,528
hundreds of meters.

59
00:05:00,207 --> 00:05:01,447
I don't know. I just got here.

60
00:05:01,447 --> 00:05:02,606
I need to ask around.

61
00:05:03,647 --> 00:05:04,447
What's going on?

62
00:05:15,846 --> 00:05:17,807
Where exactly did you
find the wallet and watch?

63
00:05:18,127 --> 00:05:19,647
Right under that tree up ahead.

64
00:05:21,846 --> 00:05:22,846
Roughly what time?

65
00:05:23,207 --> 00:05:24,526
Don't remember the exact time.

66
00:05:24,726 --> 00:05:25,966
Found anything else?

67
00:05:26,366 --> 00:05:26,966
No.

68
00:05:34,567 --> 00:05:35,966
Wang Tong, found something.

69
00:05:40,606 --> 00:05:41,327
Dig.

70
00:05:41,647 --> 00:05:42,207
Yes.

71
00:05:58,286 --> 00:05:59,486
Hello, Captain Leng.

72
00:05:59,647 --> 00:06:01,767
No body has been found here
at Central Park so far.

73
00:06:02,286 --> 00:06:04,007
This spot is a blind spot for cameras.

74
00:06:04,007 --> 00:06:04,846
Capture nothing.

75
00:06:05,687 --> 00:06:06,687
I asked around.

76
00:06:06,687 --> 00:06:09,606
Footage from park entrances, exits,
and main paths clears weekly.

77
00:06:09,846 --> 00:06:12,046
Even if they captured anything,
it's likely long gone.

78
00:06:13,726 --> 00:06:15,327
Okay, got it.

79
00:06:21,944 --> 00:06:24,920
(Cheng Jianmin)

80
00:06:28,152 --> 00:06:30,392
(Yunxi Entrepreneur Cheng Jianmin,
Chairman of Longcheng Real Estate)

81
00:06:30,392 --> 00:06:32,760
(Yunxi's New Commercial Landmark,
Stellar Center, Officially Opens)

82
00:06:48,327 --> 00:06:49,127
Hello, Mom.

83
00:06:49,447 --> 00:06:50,647
Are you doing okay overseas?

84
00:06:53,366 --> 00:06:54,286
I'm doing fine.

85
00:06:54,926 --> 00:06:55,767
Where's Dad?

86
00:06:56,166 --> 00:06:57,327
I have something to ask him.

87
00:06:58,486 --> 00:06:59,687
It was quite a while ago.

88
00:07:00,327 --> 00:07:02,046
Probably when I was
in elementary school.

89
00:08:49,688 --> 00:08:51,448
(Demolish)

90
00:08:56,047 --> 00:08:58,287
How can we work then?

91
00:08:58,687 --> 00:08:59,966
Might as well just move out.

92
00:09:02,006 --> 00:09:03,006
Jiang Yue, you're back.

93
00:09:08,966 --> 00:09:10,366
Anyway, I took tomorrow off.

94
00:09:10,846 --> 00:09:12,047
Few orders lately.

95
00:09:12,047 --> 00:09:13,752
The firework factory
will go under anyway.

96
00:09:16,376 --> 00:09:18,730
(Notice to Vacate by Deadline
Baoquan Fireworks Factory)

97
00:09:23,251 --> 00:09:28,920
(Fireworks)

98
00:09:30,407 --> 00:09:32,886
(Black-heart factory!
Deadly production!)

99
00:09:33,167 --> 00:09:35,606
(Negligent murder! We demand justice!)

100
00:09:36,646 --> 00:09:39,366
(Black-heart factory!
Deadly production!)

101
00:09:39,687 --> 00:09:42,087
(Negligent murder! We demand justice!)

102
00:09:43,527 --> 00:09:46,246
(Black-heart factory!
Deadly production!)

103
00:09:46,567 --> 00:09:48,807
(Negligent murder! We demand justice!)

104
00:09:51,167 --> 00:09:53,646
(Black-heart factory!
Deadly production!)

105
00:09:54,047 --> 00:09:56,407
(Negligent murder! We demand justice!)

106
00:09:57,527 --> 00:10:00,246
(Black-heart factory!
Deadly production!)

107
00:10:00,567 --> 00:10:02,766
(Negligent murder! We demand justice!)

108
00:10:04,246 --> 00:10:06,966
(Black-heart factory!
Deadly production!)

109
00:10:07,126 --> 00:10:09,606
(Negligent murder! We demand justice!)

110
00:10:09,606 --> 00:10:10,287
Go.

111
00:10:26,366 --> 00:10:27,047
Jiang Yue.

112
00:10:27,567 --> 00:10:28,687
Come for dinner.

113
00:10:30,126 --> 00:10:31,287
Give me your backpack.

114
00:10:32,927 --> 00:10:34,287
Why are you back so late?

115
00:10:39,207 --> 00:10:40,006
Jiang Yue.

116
00:10:40,327 --> 00:10:41,407
Watch out!

117
00:10:47,486 --> 00:10:49,006
Such a good factory.,

118
00:10:49,006 --> 00:10:51,087
why did it explode?

119
00:10:51,486 --> 00:10:53,087
- What a shame.
- Really.

120
00:10:53,087 --> 00:10:55,167
A factory's just gone like that.

121
00:10:55,167 --> 00:10:57,486
Right, why did it explode?

122
00:10:57,927 --> 00:11:00,606
That child was so young. Right?

123
00:11:00,606 --> 00:11:01,527
Exactly.

124
00:11:02,207 --> 00:11:03,287
So pitiful.

125
00:11:03,646 --> 00:11:04,407
Right.

126
00:11:16,486 --> 00:11:18,126
I knew that factory was a time bomb.

127
00:11:18,126 --> 00:11:19,207
Please restrain your grief.

128
00:11:19,207 --> 00:11:20,287
Look on the bright side.

129
00:11:20,846 --> 00:11:22,126
We're here for you.

130
00:11:23,407 --> 00:11:26,327
I heard the factory owner and his wife
were inside when it happened.

131
00:11:26,486 --> 00:11:27,807
I heard they were blown apart.

132
00:11:29,606 --> 00:11:30,407
How pitiful.

133
00:11:30,407 --> 00:11:32,088
Their child was only
in elementary school.

134
00:12:29,327 --> 00:12:30,126
Jiang Yue!

135
00:12:31,246 --> 00:12:32,167
Jiang Yue!

136
00:12:32,846 --> 00:12:33,646
Jiang Yue!

137
00:12:34,366 --> 00:12:37,047
Jiang Yue! Where has that kid gone?

138
00:12:37,047 --> 00:12:38,167
Come with me.

139
00:13:28,886 --> 00:13:29,527
Master.

140
00:13:33,846 --> 00:13:35,126
I made some inquiries.

141
00:13:35,846 --> 00:13:37,927
Cheng Jianmin's business grew so big

142
00:13:38,447 --> 00:13:39,807
largely because

143
00:13:39,966 --> 00:13:42,447
he developed
the Dongfeng Cultural Plaza project.

144
00:13:43,006 --> 00:13:46,966
Back then, a firework factory
on that land refused to relocate.

145
00:13:47,327 --> 00:13:48,567
The project stalled.

146
00:13:49,167 --> 00:13:50,886
Then that factory exploded.

147
00:13:51,006 --> 00:13:52,646
The owner and his wife
died in the blast.

148
00:13:52,646 --> 00:13:53,567
The factory closed.

149
00:13:53,567 --> 00:13:56,248
The black powder

150
00:13:57,112 --> 00:13:59,726
used in the urban village arson
came from fireworks.

151
00:14:00,807 --> 00:14:03,527
You suspect Cheng Jianmin
rigged it back then?

152
00:14:04,527 --> 00:14:08,366
That factory's production safety permit
had just expired at that moment,

153
00:14:08,567 --> 00:14:10,807
so the incident was ruled
an industrial accident.

154
00:14:11,447 --> 00:14:13,167
But what I heard is

155
00:14:13,366 --> 00:14:16,606
Cheng Jianmin bribed a worker
to trigger the explosion.

156
00:14:17,447 --> 00:14:18,726
Is this intel reliable?

157
00:14:19,966 --> 00:14:23,646
My dad's friend
was one of the project partners then.

158
00:14:24,006 --> 00:14:27,366
He heard Cheng Jianmin
bribed a factory worker

159
00:14:27,366 --> 00:14:28,408
to trigger the explosion,

160
00:14:28,527 --> 00:14:30,606
using a cell phone
to manipulate when to drop

161
00:14:30,606 --> 00:14:31,927
the sodium metal into water.

162
00:14:32,047 --> 00:14:34,407
With all the fireworks stored there,

163
00:14:34,687 --> 00:14:36,486
the phone was completely incinerated,

164
00:14:37,287 --> 00:14:39,366
and that worker had an alibi.

165
00:14:39,527 --> 00:14:42,246
It's very difficult to verify
with the techniques at that time.

166
00:14:42,807 --> 00:14:43,966
Years passed,

167
00:14:43,966 --> 00:14:47,327
that worker killed himself, leaving
a suicide note confessing his guilt.

168
00:14:47,567 --> 00:14:50,366
The note detailed how he did it.

169
00:14:50,366 --> 00:14:52,886
He didn't name who hired him,

170
00:14:53,006 --> 00:14:55,207
but people suspected Cheng Jianmin.

171
00:15:01,207 --> 00:15:05,207
It happened over 20 years ago.

172
00:15:06,447 --> 00:15:08,927
Even if Cheng Jianmin was involved,

173
00:15:10,207 --> 00:15:13,807
we can't find any solid evidence now.

174
00:15:16,966 --> 00:15:21,126
The accident caused the death
of the factory owner and his wife.

175
00:15:22,006 --> 00:15:26,687
If their family knew the role
Cheng Jianmin played in this accident,

176
00:15:28,087 --> 00:15:29,766
they'd have sufficient reason to kill.

177
00:15:33,167 --> 00:15:34,726
It's been so long already.

178
00:15:35,527 --> 00:15:37,886
Even if someone held a grudge
against him,

179
00:15:39,006 --> 00:15:40,527
why wait so long?

180
00:15:43,966 --> 00:15:46,126
Maybe they just found out,

181
00:15:47,447 --> 00:15:51,126
or something changed their mind.

182
00:15:53,087 --> 00:15:53,726
Master.

183
00:15:54,846 --> 00:15:58,047
The killer chose to blow up
the rental house in the same way.

184
00:15:58,047 --> 00:16:00,486
It points to the victims' family
seeking revenge.

185
00:16:00,606 --> 00:16:03,207
Cheng Jianmin's death
was just the beginning.

186
00:16:10,712 --> 00:16:12,600
(Yu Xiao'ou Case)

187
00:17:07,686 --> 00:17:08,926
Hello.

188
00:17:09,646 --> 00:17:10,646
Why are you still alive?

189
00:17:10,846 --> 00:17:12,166
Why don't you just die?

190
00:17:13,406 --> 00:17:16,007
People like you deserve
to be struck by lightning.

191
00:17:16,567 --> 00:17:17,767
Watch out when it storms.

192
00:17:34,846 --> 00:17:36,007
Hello, this is the...

193
00:17:36,567 --> 00:17:38,206
Hello?

194
00:17:39,446 --> 00:17:40,967
People are so rude nowadays.

195
00:17:41,087 --> 00:17:42,886
Hanging up mid-sentence.

196
00:17:49,926 --> 00:17:50,646
How's it going?

197
00:17:50,646 --> 00:17:51,406
Found any?

198
00:17:53,406 --> 00:17:55,166
I've still got way to go.
What about you?

199
00:17:55,886 --> 00:17:56,606
Come on.

200
00:17:56,807 --> 00:17:59,247
I've been transferred for several times.

201
00:17:59,247 --> 00:18:00,807
Wonder if I can even reach the person.

202
00:18:03,807 --> 00:18:04,846
Hello.

203
00:18:04,846 --> 00:18:05,727
Yes, hello.

204
00:18:05,727 --> 00:18:06,886
Police.

205
00:18:07,047 --> 00:18:08,166
Are you Yang Zheng?

206
00:18:08,846 --> 00:18:09,567
Check it.

207
00:18:10,087 --> 00:18:12,886
Here are the hot social events
recently I summarized

208
00:18:12,926 --> 00:18:16,007
based on your requirements.

209
00:18:16,248 --> 00:18:18,366
Considering the preparation time
the killer needs,

210
00:18:18,366 --> 00:18:20,727
I've ruled out those
happened in the past week.

211
00:18:24,846 --> 00:18:26,126
Can't rule out more?

212
00:18:30,967 --> 00:18:32,087
I wish.

213
00:18:32,446 --> 00:18:35,446
Think about it. If we rule out more
and skip checking it,

214
00:18:35,846 --> 00:18:37,166
then those two really act,

215
00:18:37,166 --> 00:18:38,166
whose blame is that?

216
00:18:40,606 --> 00:18:41,446
So many.

217
00:18:41,767 --> 00:18:43,646
Screening them one by one
isn't practical.

218
00:18:44,646 --> 00:18:46,366
The team's main focus right now

219
00:18:46,567 --> 00:18:49,446
is on finding people connected
to the firework factory explosion.

220
00:18:49,926 --> 00:18:51,727
What do we do?
We still have to screen them.

221
00:18:52,287 --> 00:18:53,926
But I have another finding.

222
00:19:01,686 --> 00:19:03,287
One can change his clothing.

223
00:19:03,287 --> 00:19:04,807
But under normal walking conditions,

224
00:19:04,807 --> 00:19:06,287
stride length, walking posture,

225
00:19:06,287 --> 00:19:08,967
and body sway patterns
don't change easily.

226
00:19:09,406 --> 00:19:11,206
I think your theory is correct.

227
00:19:15,287 --> 00:19:17,406
Gao Liang and his girlfriend
are the same person.

228
00:19:19,527 --> 00:19:22,287
The forensic unit analyzed
the gait of both suspects

229
00:19:22,327 --> 00:19:23,832
and thinks they're the same person.

230
00:19:23,967 --> 00:19:27,487
This also explains why these two
have never appeared at the same time.

231
00:19:28,007 --> 00:19:30,287
It's inferred this person's
actual identity is male,

232
00:19:30,287 --> 00:19:31,567
over 180 cm tall,

233
00:19:31,686 --> 00:19:32,487
and relatively thin.

234
00:19:33,767 --> 00:19:35,287
Here's the suspect profile.

235
00:19:37,087 --> 00:19:38,366
Through profile comparison,

236
00:19:38,527 --> 00:19:39,640
Jiang Yue, the only son

237
00:19:39,640 --> 00:19:41,880
of the couple killed
in the firework factory explosion,

238
00:19:41,880 --> 00:19:43,606
shows high similarity to the profile.

239
00:19:44,487 --> 00:19:45,646
Jiang Yue is out of contact.

240
00:19:46,007 --> 00:19:48,527
He was in fifth grade
when the explosion happened.

241
00:19:48,527 --> 00:19:49,247
And he was there.

242
00:19:49,366 --> 00:19:51,446
He survived
because of his mother's protection.

243
00:19:51,646 --> 00:19:54,287
Then, he was raised
by his maternal grandparents.

244
00:19:55,366 --> 00:19:57,047
This is Jiang Yue's ID photo.

245
00:19:57,926 --> 00:20:00,327
How's Jiang Yue going?

246
00:20:03,512 --> 00:20:04,600
His maternal grandparents

247
00:20:04,600 --> 00:20:07,047
passed away one after the other
before he started university.

248
00:20:07,287 --> 00:20:10,047
Jiang Yue vanished
after graduating from university.

249
00:20:10,807 --> 00:20:14,406
It's not easy for someone
to leave no trace these days.

250
00:20:14,406 --> 00:20:15,967
Unless he never uses an ID card,

251
00:20:16,087 --> 00:20:17,767
and uses only cash.

252
00:20:18,366 --> 00:20:19,846
But that's unrealistic.

253
00:20:20,886 --> 00:20:23,727
So he's been using
someone else's identity.

254
00:20:24,327 --> 00:20:25,807
Stuck in a dead end again.

255
00:20:25,807 --> 00:20:28,686
Check Jiang Yue's contacts now.

256
00:20:28,807 --> 00:20:32,527
Before graduation,
Jiang Yue must have lived a normal life.

257
00:20:33,487 --> 00:20:34,727
There must be some clues.

258
00:20:36,807 --> 00:20:37,446
Let's go.

259
00:20:43,767 --> 00:20:44,686
Open up!

260
00:20:47,646 --> 00:20:48,807
I know you're in there.

261
00:20:54,487 --> 00:20:55,527
If you don't come out,

262
00:20:55,527 --> 00:20:56,886
I'll open this door and come in!

263
00:21:02,886 --> 00:21:03,926
Open the door now!

264
00:21:05,087 --> 00:21:05,926
Do you hear me?

265
00:21:17,126 --> 00:21:17,926
Open the door!

266
00:21:19,606 --> 00:21:20,926
Don't try to fool me!

267
00:21:31,247 --> 00:21:33,047
How dare you
install this thing on the door?

268
00:21:33,686 --> 00:21:36,366
If you damage my door,
I'll deduct it from your deposit!

269
00:21:37,886 --> 00:21:39,206
I'm here to notify you.

270
00:21:39,206 --> 00:21:40,527
I'm not renting this place out.

271
00:21:40,846 --> 00:21:42,206
Pack up and leave soon.

272
00:21:43,686 --> 00:21:45,446
I've paid the rent on time.

273
00:21:45,446 --> 00:21:47,007
I don't want to rent it out anymore.

274
00:21:47,007 --> 00:21:48,406
No more excuses.

275
00:21:49,007 --> 00:21:50,606
But we signed a contract.

276
00:21:50,606 --> 00:21:51,846
Forget the contract.

277
00:21:51,846 --> 00:21:52,606
Let me tell you.

278
00:21:52,606 --> 00:21:53,606
This is my house.

279
00:21:53,606 --> 00:21:54,406
I just don't want

280
00:21:54,406 --> 00:21:56,247
to rent it out anymore. So what?

281
00:21:56,807 --> 00:21:58,646
You can't be so unreasonable.

282
00:21:59,366 --> 00:22:00,926
Do I need to be reasonable with you?

283
00:22:01,646 --> 00:22:04,727
I only rented to you
because your innocent look fooled me.

284
00:22:05,126 --> 00:22:07,406
You seemed clean, fair-skinned,

285
00:22:07,606 --> 00:22:08,727
quiet and well-behaved,

286
00:22:08,807 --> 00:22:10,527
but you're actually a shameless villain!

287
00:22:11,767 --> 00:22:13,087
If I had seen you

288
00:22:13,087 --> 00:22:13,967
on the news,

289
00:22:14,166 --> 00:22:15,727
I would never rent my house to you.

290
00:22:16,406 --> 00:22:17,487
Enough.

291
00:22:17,487 --> 00:22:18,846
Enough talk.

292
00:22:18,846 --> 00:22:19,686
In short,

293
00:22:19,686 --> 00:22:20,967
get out of here

294
00:22:21,487 --> 00:22:22,446
by tomorrow morning.

295
00:22:23,166 --> 00:22:25,527
Not kicking you out right now
is already showing you mercy.

296
00:22:28,327 --> 00:22:29,406
Jinx!

297
00:22:29,406 --> 00:22:30,606
Bad luck to meet you!

298
00:22:54,327 --> 00:22:55,446
What a pile of trash!

299
00:22:56,967 --> 00:22:58,366
All this bad luck!

300
00:22:59,686 --> 00:23:00,487
Leave!

301
00:23:00,567 --> 00:23:01,327
Get out of here!

302
00:23:02,126 --> 00:23:02,967
Oh, my.

303
00:23:04,126 --> 00:23:05,496
I'll kick out of all the bad luck.

304
00:23:07,007 --> 00:23:08,327
Get away from here.

305
00:23:09,446 --> 00:23:10,366
Oh, my.

306
00:23:15,166 --> 00:23:16,126
You people, move!

307
00:23:19,047 --> 00:23:21,126
Renting to this jinx this time,

308
00:23:21,126 --> 00:23:22,087
what terrible luck!

309
00:23:22,406 --> 00:23:23,767
I have to be more careful.

310
00:24:30,168 --> 00:24:38,747
(Rent/Buy Property, Real Estate Agent)

311
00:25:33,967 --> 00:25:34,487
Hello.

312
00:25:35,807 --> 00:25:36,327
Hello.

313
00:25:38,487 --> 00:25:39,206
Mom.

314
00:25:40,606 --> 00:25:41,926
How dare you call back?

315
00:25:46,406 --> 00:25:48,126
I need money for rent.

316
00:25:48,606 --> 00:25:49,327
Money?

317
00:25:49,327 --> 00:25:50,646
How dare you even ask?

318
00:25:50,767 --> 00:25:52,406
You deserve it!

319
00:25:52,487 --> 00:25:53,886
I won't give you a single cent.

320
00:25:53,886 --> 00:25:56,727
After such a disgraceful act,
you still have the nerve to call?

321
00:25:56,727 --> 00:25:57,567
Let me tell you.

322
00:25:57,567 --> 00:25:59,047
You deserve to starve to death.

323
00:25:59,047 --> 00:25:59,926
Don't bother me again.

324
00:26:08,686 --> 00:26:10,287
This rent is so cheap.

325
00:26:10,287 --> 00:26:11,606
Wonder what kind of place it is.

326
00:26:12,206 --> 00:26:13,047
Must be bad quality.

327
00:26:13,047 --> 00:26:14,247
There must be a catch.

328
00:26:14,606 --> 00:26:15,567
Let's go check that one.

329
00:26:15,567 --> 00:26:17,166
Okay, that one over there, right?

330
00:26:27,032 --> 00:26:32,504
(Now Renting!)

331
00:26:55,206 --> 00:26:56,886
Please take a look.

332
00:26:56,886 --> 00:26:57,567
Thanks.

333
00:27:01,007 --> 00:27:02,406
Please take a look.

334
00:27:03,206 --> 00:27:03,926
Thanks.

335
00:27:04,606 --> 00:27:05,406
Hello.

336
00:27:06,166 --> 00:27:07,487
I'd like to ask

337
00:27:08,087 --> 00:27:10,487
if it's really this cheap.

338
00:27:12,166 --> 00:27:13,567
This listing is new.

339
00:27:13,926 --> 00:27:15,007
The apartment is fine.

340
00:27:15,487 --> 00:27:17,807
But it's a bit out of the way,
not very lively.

341
00:27:18,527 --> 00:27:19,727
A bit far from the subway.

342
00:27:20,287 --> 00:27:21,446
It's fine. I'll take it.

343
00:27:24,686 --> 00:27:25,646
Don't rush.

344
00:27:26,206 --> 00:27:27,967
You're looking for a place cheap?

345
00:27:29,366 --> 00:27:29,967
How about this?

346
00:27:30,767 --> 00:27:32,087
Let me show you the place.

347
00:27:32,206 --> 00:27:34,487
If it doesn't suit you,
I'll find you another.

348
00:27:35,047 --> 00:27:35,846
Okay.

349
00:27:36,886 --> 00:27:37,686
Let me help.

350
00:27:38,327 --> 00:27:39,126
Thanks.

351
00:27:51,087 --> 00:27:53,646
Yue and I shared bunk beds in college.

352
00:27:53,767 --> 00:27:56,166
We dorm mates started
a business together junior year.

353
00:27:57,087 --> 00:27:58,686
We were computer science majors,

354
00:27:58,967 --> 00:28:00,727
so we worked on a program together.

355
00:28:01,166 --> 00:28:02,606
It had great potential back then.

356
00:28:02,606 --> 00:28:04,926
Several investors were quite interested.

357
00:28:06,007 --> 00:28:09,527
But we were too naive

358
00:28:09,967 --> 00:28:11,846
and got scammed by an alleged investor.

359
00:28:13,126 --> 00:28:14,126
He took our money

360
00:28:14,567 --> 00:28:16,287
and stole our intellectual property.

361
00:28:16,767 --> 00:28:18,007
Of course, we didn't accept it.

362
00:28:19,487 --> 00:28:23,366
But facing reality, we had to let it go.

363
00:28:23,967 --> 00:28:25,366
Besides, we were about to graduate.

364
00:28:25,686 --> 00:28:26,646
Finding housing,

365
00:28:26,807 --> 00:28:28,166
job hunting, studying abroad...

366
00:28:28,166 --> 00:28:29,287
It was overwhelming.

367
00:28:29,767 --> 00:28:31,846
So we didn't have the time to pursue it.

368
00:28:32,567 --> 00:28:34,327
Yue didn't complain much at the time.

369
00:28:34,886 --> 00:28:38,926
But secretly, he found a way
to get back at that guy.

370
00:28:40,007 --> 00:28:42,527
Jiang Yue is quite vindictive.

371
00:28:43,087 --> 00:28:44,126
What did he do?

372
00:28:46,206 --> 00:28:48,166
I'm not entirely sure.

373
00:28:50,406 --> 00:28:54,366
I just heard he found
some online scammers

374
00:28:55,087 --> 00:28:56,567
to deceive that guy.

375
00:28:56,967 --> 00:28:59,686
So Jiang Yue
was involved in online fraud?

376
00:29:00,126 --> 00:29:02,606
Well, I-I don't know about that.

377
00:29:03,406 --> 00:29:05,247
Did you contact after graduation?

378
00:29:05,487 --> 00:29:06,287
No.

379
00:29:06,967 --> 00:29:08,166
Before graduation,

380
00:29:08,287 --> 00:29:11,846
Yue gave us back all the money we lost,

381
00:29:12,366 --> 00:29:14,606
then he just vanished

382
00:29:14,886 --> 00:29:15,886
without a trace.

383
00:29:16,727 --> 00:29:18,606
We dorm mates all worried about him.

384
00:29:19,366 --> 00:29:23,247
And we knew he only had
his grandparents left.

385
00:29:23,366 --> 00:29:24,487
His parents were gone.

386
00:29:26,527 --> 00:29:27,527
It was tough for him.

387
00:29:27,727 --> 00:29:29,166
Wonder how he's been doing.

388
00:29:29,287 --> 00:29:32,767
What do you know
about his parents' deaths?

389
00:29:33,206 --> 00:29:34,446
I heard it was an accident.

390
00:29:35,487 --> 00:29:36,767
Don't know more than that.

391
00:29:37,567 --> 00:29:39,087
Yue was usually quiet,

392
00:29:39,686 --> 00:29:41,446
but deep down he was quite proud.

393
00:29:41,926 --> 00:29:43,047
About his parents,

394
00:29:44,406 --> 00:29:46,886
if he didn't bring it up,
we wouldn't ask, right?

395
00:29:49,166 --> 00:29:51,287
Officer, I do remember one thing.

396
00:29:52,767 --> 00:29:54,727
Yue had a small box.

397
00:29:55,287 --> 00:29:56,487
It was quite ornate.

398
00:29:56,487 --> 00:29:58,327
I don't know what was inside.

399
00:29:58,366 --> 00:30:00,606
Just that his mother left it for him.

400
00:30:06,926 --> 00:30:07,767
Thank you.

401
00:30:12,767 --> 00:30:13,646
What do you think?

402
00:30:14,206 --> 00:30:16,406
If Jiang Yue
was involved in online fraud,

403
00:30:16,807 --> 00:30:20,366
that explains all those IDs he had.

404
00:30:22,967 --> 00:30:24,967
This guy is resilient,

405
00:30:26,047 --> 00:30:26,846
determined,

406
00:30:28,166 --> 00:30:29,527
and highly driven.

407
00:30:30,166 --> 00:30:33,846
It's been a while
since Liu Xiaofeng was killed.

408
00:30:34,926 --> 00:30:36,606
Given his capability,

409
00:30:37,567 --> 00:30:39,767
he's very likely
already looking for the next target,

410
00:30:40,327 --> 00:30:41,686
or he's already on it.

411
00:30:45,126 --> 00:30:48,886
How's your forum investigation going
with Long?

412
00:30:50,967 --> 00:30:53,126
Quite a few potential targets
identified so far.

413
00:30:53,366 --> 00:30:56,527
But if you want me to say the one
who is most likely his next target,

414
00:30:56,527 --> 00:30:58,247
I truly can't do it.

415
00:30:58,247 --> 00:31:00,047
I really can't.

416
00:31:03,406 --> 00:31:05,007
Can you stop walking back and forth?

417
00:31:05,247 --> 00:31:05,886
Making me dizzy.

418
00:31:07,087 --> 00:31:08,926
I am the dizzy one.

419
00:31:09,606 --> 00:31:10,807
The most I can do

420
00:31:10,967 --> 00:31:14,166
is to narrow the range
just a tiny bit more.

421
00:31:14,366 --> 00:31:15,007
Just a tiny bit.

422
00:31:15,007 --> 00:31:17,247
Long has been overwhelmed
these past two days.

423
00:31:17,567 --> 00:31:19,206
He's been so focused on this

424
00:31:19,366 --> 00:31:20,886
and hasn't even gone home.

425
00:31:21,926 --> 00:31:23,767
Look at how red his eyes are,

426
00:31:23,886 --> 00:31:25,686
like a little rabbit.

427
00:31:26,727 --> 00:31:27,446
Long.

428
00:31:28,247 --> 00:31:32,406
Tell us. Tell us about
that narrowed range.

429
00:31:33,007 --> 00:31:33,886
Just say it.

430
00:31:34,126 --> 00:31:35,126
Okay.

431
00:31:37,926 --> 00:31:40,366
I sorted events by online popularity.

432
00:31:40,366 --> 00:31:43,606
The top ten most-viewed events.

433
00:31:43,606 --> 00:31:46,166
Only three
fit the suspect's selection criteria.

434
00:31:46,446 --> 00:31:49,400
First is the event of the female intern

435
00:31:49,400 --> 00:31:52,287
sexually harassed
by a famous journalist.

436
00:31:52,606 --> 00:31:56,527
Second is the female grad student
who protected her best friend

437
00:31:56,527 --> 00:31:58,327
was killed by that friend's boyfriend.

438
00:31:58,327 --> 00:32:01,527
Third is a seventy-year-old elderly
abandoned by his three sons

439
00:32:01,527 --> 00:32:02,767
and left homeless.

440
00:32:03,007 --> 00:32:06,767
If the suspect selects targets
based on popularity,

441
00:32:06,767 --> 00:32:09,886
it's highly likely
one of these three events.

442
00:32:10,166 --> 00:32:11,606
How can you be sure

443
00:32:11,606 --> 00:32:14,646
the suspect chooses targets
by popularity?

444
00:32:14,967 --> 00:32:16,166
I reviewed the previous events

445
00:32:16,166 --> 00:32:18,767
of Zhou Lianqin, Wen Yong,
and Liu Xiaofeng.

446
00:32:19,087 --> 00:32:19,767
These three

447
00:32:19,767 --> 00:32:23,166
ranked in the top-ten social focus
during their time.

448
00:32:23,166 --> 00:32:25,447
Among the events that ranked
in the top-ten social focus,

449
00:32:25,447 --> 00:32:28,406
only two or three fit the suspect's

450
00:32:28,487 --> 00:32:31,247
self-proclaimed role
as a justice enforcer.

451
00:32:31,967 --> 00:32:35,366
So I'm confident in this narrowed rage.

452
00:32:35,366 --> 00:32:37,727
But I couldn't narrow it down further

453
00:32:38,126 --> 00:32:39,646
to pinpoint his exact target.

454
00:32:41,206 --> 00:32:41,846
Good.

455
00:32:42,126 --> 00:32:43,967
I'll report to Chief Xu.

456
00:32:44,007 --> 00:32:46,807
We'll immediately investigate
all parties in these three cases.

457
00:32:47,487 --> 00:32:48,166
Okay.

458
00:32:48,487 --> 00:32:49,567
Move! Hurry!

459
00:32:50,287 --> 00:32:51,087
Get moving!

460
00:33:46,727 --> 00:33:47,366
You're awake.

461
00:33:59,487 --> 00:34:00,206
It's you?

462
00:34:02,007 --> 00:34:03,126
You're not the agent.

463
00:34:06,686 --> 00:34:08,487
You've been hiding for days,

464
00:34:10,007 --> 00:34:11,766
yet your guard is still this weak.

465
00:34:14,206 --> 00:34:16,407
No wonder you got kicked out
like a stray.

466
00:34:21,087 --> 00:34:22,286
The door is behind me.

467
00:34:24,166 --> 00:34:25,447
Leaving is easy.

468
00:34:28,367 --> 00:34:31,087
Just fulfill one small request for me.

469
00:34:33,567 --> 00:34:34,567
What do you want?

470
00:34:36,806 --> 00:34:37,487
Take a guess.

471
00:34:38,887 --> 00:34:39,806
I don't know.

472
00:34:39,806 --> 00:34:40,806
Who are you?

473
00:34:42,887 --> 00:34:44,166
Don't rush.

474
00:34:45,047 --> 00:34:46,527
I haven't said anything yet.

475
00:34:51,726 --> 00:34:52,487
It's simple.

476
00:34:53,766 --> 00:34:56,606
Haven't forgotten
the Yu Xiao'ou case, have you?

477
00:34:59,527 --> 00:35:01,646
Tell the truth
about Yu Xiao'ou's murder,

478
00:35:02,887 --> 00:35:03,806
then I'll let you go.

479
00:35:04,927 --> 00:35:05,567
Deal?

480
00:35:08,567 --> 00:35:09,407
I did.

481
00:35:09,407 --> 00:35:10,286
I said it.

482
00:35:10,407 --> 00:35:12,367
What I said in court was the truth.

483
00:35:14,766 --> 00:35:15,806
Chances are limited.

484
00:35:16,527 --> 00:35:17,927
Think it over.

485
00:35:31,606 --> 00:35:33,567
Regarding the elderly
abandoned by his children,

486
00:35:33,567 --> 00:35:35,246
all involved parties have been located.

487
00:35:35,527 --> 00:35:39,246
Community staff are temporarily
caring for the elderly.

488
00:35:40,126 --> 00:35:43,367
Organizations like
Women's Federation, Civil Affairs,

489
00:35:43,367 --> 00:35:46,447
and local police station are

490
00:35:46,606 --> 00:35:50,606
working together to mediate
between the elderly and her children.

491
00:35:51,326 --> 00:35:53,766
They're also educating them
about legal obligations,

492
00:35:53,766 --> 00:35:56,806
making them understand
children must support their parents.

493
00:35:58,206 --> 00:35:58,927
By the way,

494
00:35:58,927 --> 00:36:02,087
about the intern's sexual harassment
case against her supervisor,

495
00:36:02,126 --> 00:36:03,646
the girl hired a lawyer

496
00:36:04,166 --> 00:36:05,606
and sued the man in court.

497
00:36:05,606 --> 00:36:07,326
Though the man hasn't admitted guilt,

498
00:36:07,527 --> 00:36:08,927
he also hired a lawyer.

499
00:36:09,087 --> 00:36:12,567
His workplace suspended him

500
00:36:12,567 --> 00:36:14,166
due to negative publicity.

501
00:36:14,166 --> 00:36:16,166
Both sides are proceeding legally now.

502
00:36:17,407 --> 00:36:19,286
Are both parties currently safe?

503
00:36:19,726 --> 00:36:20,286
Yes.

504
00:36:20,286 --> 00:36:23,606
Both insist no one resembling
Jiang Yue approached them.

505
00:36:24,166 --> 00:36:26,047
Zhang Wei, the murderer
in Yu Xiao'ou's case,

506
00:36:26,166 --> 00:36:27,487
is currently in prison.

507
00:36:28,007 --> 00:36:30,887
Yu Xiao'ou and Zhang Wei's families
are out of town.

508
00:36:30,887 --> 00:36:32,126
We've contacted them.

509
00:36:32,567 --> 00:36:36,087
The only one who could not be reached
is the key witness Xia Tian.

510
00:36:36,686 --> 00:36:39,087
So her boyfriend was the murderer?

511
00:36:39,927 --> 00:36:40,567
Yes.

512
00:36:40,567 --> 00:36:42,606
All three were grad school classmates.

513
00:36:42,606 --> 00:36:45,126
Zhang Wei and Xia Tian were dating.

514
00:36:45,126 --> 00:36:46,447
Xia Tian tried to break up.

515
00:36:46,447 --> 00:36:47,286
Zhang Wei disagreed.

516
00:36:47,286 --> 00:36:50,206
As Xia Tian's best friend,
Yu Xiao'ou stepped in to mediate.

517
00:36:50,206 --> 00:36:52,606
Unexpectedly, Zhang Wei
brought a weapon.

518
00:36:53,166 --> 00:36:56,007
In the end, Zhang Wei killed Yu Xiao'ou.

519
00:36:56,527 --> 00:36:58,367
I think I've heard of this case.

520
00:36:58,367 --> 00:37:00,088
Handled by the neighboring province,
right?

521
00:37:00,166 --> 00:37:02,206
Among those involved,
only Xia Tian is from Yunxi.

522
00:37:02,367 --> 00:37:04,487
And she has been enduring
persistent cyberbullying.

523
00:37:04,487 --> 00:37:05,496
After the case concluded,

524
00:37:05,496 --> 00:37:07,480
she suspended her schooling
and returned to Yunxi.

525
00:37:07,686 --> 00:37:08,487
Cyberbullying?

526
00:37:08,567 --> 00:37:09,206
Yes.

527
00:37:10,126 --> 00:37:13,487
Many believe Yu Xiao'ou
lost her life for Xia Tian.

528
00:37:13,487 --> 00:37:14,686
She took the knife for her.

529
00:37:14,806 --> 00:37:17,720
But Xia Tian denied this
in her court testimony.

530
00:37:17,720 --> 00:37:19,704
She claimed the murderer
had planned it for long,

531
00:37:19,704 --> 00:37:21,326
and Yu Xiao'ou was the target.

532
00:37:22,087 --> 00:37:24,326
The court accepted Xia Tian's testimony,

533
00:37:24,326 --> 00:37:26,887
indicating there was solid evidence.

534
00:37:27,367 --> 00:37:29,087
Why are those people online
making a fuss?

535
00:37:30,527 --> 00:37:32,206
I checked this.

536
00:37:32,206 --> 00:37:34,126
There are nasty comments.

537
00:37:34,126 --> 00:37:34,967
All sorts of stuff.

538
00:37:34,967 --> 00:37:36,686
Most of these people
making a fuss online

539
00:37:36,686 --> 00:37:38,887
don't have anything serious going on.

540
00:37:38,887 --> 00:37:40,646
They're just venting their emotions,

541
00:37:40,646 --> 00:37:42,887
and don't care
what the truth of the case is.

542
00:37:42,967 --> 00:37:44,766
They're just making up nonsense,

543
00:37:44,766 --> 00:37:46,616
hitching onto the topic
and chasing the hype.

544
00:37:46,726 --> 00:37:47,367
Anyway, they're

545
00:37:47,367 --> 00:37:48,567
utilizing others' misfortunes.

546
00:37:48,567 --> 00:37:51,527
This case involves privacy,

547
00:37:52,007 --> 00:37:54,126
so many details
weren't disclosed to the public.

548
00:37:54,447 --> 00:37:58,407
In a way, that created a chance
for rumors to spread.

549
00:37:59,047 --> 00:38:02,567
If Jiang Yue believed these rumors
and felt something was fishy,

550
00:38:03,166 --> 00:38:04,967
and something happened to this girl,

551
00:38:05,567 --> 00:38:10,087
should those spreading rumors online
also bear responsibility?

552
00:38:10,967 --> 00:38:13,206
It is too early to say that.

553
00:38:14,367 --> 00:38:17,887
Right now, the most important thing
is to find her.

554
00:38:18,567 --> 00:38:19,407
Get moving now!

555
00:38:19,407 --> 00:38:20,007
Got it.

556
00:38:20,007 --> 00:38:21,047
- Okay.
- Okay.

557
00:42:29,529 --> 00:42:33,022
♪Replacing the weight of tears
with that of sweat♪

558
00:42:36,816 --> 00:42:42,137
♪Covering the gunshot's sound
with wounds♪

559
00:42:44,210 --> 00:42:49,064
♪No one is born unyielding and strong♪

560
00:42:49,870 --> 00:42:53,017
♪But because someone
always rushes ahead♪

561
00:42:53,017 --> 00:42:56,121
♪To shield us from the storm♪

562
00:42:58,777 --> 00:43:03,911
♪When every extraordinary act
becomes routine♪

563
00:43:05,881 --> 00:43:11,513
♪Just to polish the badge
upon their shoulder♪

564
00:43:13,273 --> 00:43:16,857
♪Like light surging unseen
through the night♪

565
00:43:18,009 --> 00:43:25,449
♪Converging into your form♪

566
00:43:25,881 --> 00:43:28,559
♪Looking up♪

567
00:43:28,559 --> 00:43:32,098
♪Such dazzling glory♪

568
00:43:33,081 --> 00:43:35,641
♪Like hope♪

569
00:43:35,641 --> 00:43:39,574
♪Reaching out its arms♪

570
00:43:40,441 --> 00:43:43,093
♪Cloaked in light♪

571
00:43:43,093 --> 00:43:47,577
♪Alone, they charge ahead♪

572
00:43:47,577 --> 00:43:50,393
♪Traversing♪

573
00:43:50,393 --> 00:43:56,904
♪The battlefield of fate♪
